# Website Component Patterns

When creating or modifying React components in the website:

## Rules

- Functional components only (no classes)
- Use TypeScript `interface` for props (not `type`)
- Named exports (not default exports)
- Use Shadcn UI + Radix UI primitives from `components/ui/`
- Mobile-first Tailwind CSS (`base`, then `md:`, `lg:`)
- Use `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classNames
- Minimize `use client` -- prefer React Server Components

## Naming

- Prop names: `isLoading`, `hasError`, `canSubmit` (auxiliary verbs)
- Component files: `kebab-case.tsx`
- Component names: `PascalCase`
- Directories: `lowercase-with-dashes`

## Pattern

```typescript
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

interface MyComponentProps {
  title: string;
  isLoading?: boolean;
  className?: string;
}

export function MyComponent({ title, isLoading = false, className }: MyComponentProps) {
  if (isLoading) return <div className={cn("animate-pulse bg-muted rounded-lg h-32", className)} />;
  return (
    <div className={cn("rounded-lg border bg-card p-6", className)}>
      <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold">{title}</h3>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Data

- NEVER include mock/fake/placeholder data
- Fetch from real APIs via hooks or server components
- Show loading skeletons and empty states for missing data
